-- Fitch Publishes Global Corporate Investor Chart Book
-- 
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 04:03AM EDT
-- None



April 28 (Reuters) - (The following statement was released by the rating agency)

Fitch Ratings has published its new quarterly Global  Corporate Investor Chart Book, which illustrates recent corporate rating trends  and structural developments across EMEA, APAC, the US and Latin America, and  provides a summary of our forecast expectations by region. The report also discusses recent corporate credit trends by region, including  how corporate ratings evolved over the past 12 months, select rating changes,  the development of global corporate credit spreads and key differentials between  CDS IRs versus Fitch's Issuer Default Ratings (IDRs). Link to Fitch Ratings' Report: Global Corporate Investor Chart Book 1Q14